// test/Lower/m3_corpus/s16/pass.test — M5 T106 / FR-030 / SC-003.
// Auto-generated golden-diff harness paired with pass.expected.mlir.
//
// Previously XFAIL'd as "permanent working-as-intended" because the
// shared input `test/sema/s16/pass.nsl` used a top-level `param_int`
// (now rejected by the tightened S16 walker). XFAIL CLOSED 2026-05-04
// by the §3.1 + S16 alignment amendment: the shared input was
// rewritten to use `#define WIDTH 8` + `%WIDTH%` splice (the
// canonical pure-NSL compile-time-constant idiom per `pp.ebnf §2.2`).
// The lowering produces a clean `nsl.reg "q" : !nsl.bits<8>` and the
// golden-diff matches.
//
// RUN: %nslc -emit=mlir %S/../../../sema/s16/pass.nsl > %t.actual.mlir
// RUN: diff %t.actual.mlir %S/pass.expected.mlir
